# HTTPS Configuration for Pi Photo Frame
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values:
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# Then rebuild: docker compose up -d --build
#
# ─── Option 1: Self-signed (default, no .env needed) ───
# Just delete or leave this file empty. Caddy will use self-signed certs.
#
# ─── Option 2: Let's Encrypt via Cloudflare ───
# DOMAIN=photos.example.com
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=your-cloudflare-api-token
#
# To get a Cloudflare API token:
#   1. Go to https://dash.cloudflare.com/profile/api-tokens
#   2. Create Token → Edit zone DNS (template)
#   3. Scope it to your domain's zone
#
# ─── Option 3: Let's Encrypt via DuckDNS (free) ───
# DOMAIN=yourname.duckdns.org
# DUCKDNS_TOKEN=your-duckdns-token
#
# To get a DuckDNS token:
#   1. Go to https://www.duckdns.org
#   2. Sign in and create a subdomain
#   3. Copy your token from the top of the page
